text: i was a bit confused in the session, do we need to setup a new dockerized envt for redash?

you can combine all the services together with airflow, dbt but that will really couple things together so having it as a separate service will be the better approach.

maybe a faster way to get started shared by Tammy --<https://joanneacademybatch6.slack.com/archives/c03t89pmjkg/p16638joanne746433569>

you'll still have all of those duplicate services, containers, and env configurations but it creates this shell script wrapper around things creating a good abstraction if you wanna keep a single compose configuration.
